What is the output of op_prob1.c C program fragment? Assume size og interger is 4 bytes.
a) 5 4
b) 6 4
c) 5 8
d) Compiler error

C standard is the language specification which is adopted by all C compilers across the globe.
C99 adopted in 1999 while C11 in 2011

According to C99 standard:
The sizeof operator yields the size (in bytes) of its operand, which may be an expression or a paranthesized name of a type.
The size is determined from the type of the operand. If the type of the operand is a variable length array type, then the operand is evaluated;
otherwise, the operand is not evaluated and the result is an integer constant.

